{{Infobox royalty | name =Armande | title = Princess of Epinoy | spouse =[[Louis, Duke of Joyeuse (1694–1724)|Louis de Melun]] | full name =Armande de La Tour d'Auvergne | house = [[House of La Tour d'Auvergne|La Tour d'Auvergne]] | father =[[Emmanuel Théodose de La Tour d'Auvergne (1668–1730)|Emmanuel Théodose de La Tour d'Auvergne]] | mother =[[Marie Armande Victoire de La Trémouille]] | birth_date ={{birth date|1697|8|28|df=y}} | death_date ={{death date and age|1717|4|13|1697|8|28|df=y}} }}
'''Armande de La Tour d'Auvergne''' (28 August 1697 &ndash; 13 April 1717) was a French noblewoman and Princess of Epinoy by marriage. She died without issue.
==Biography==
Armande was the eldest of seven children born to [[Emmanuel Théodose de La Tour d'Auvergne (1668–1730)|Emmanuel Théodose de La Tour d'Auvergne]] - sovereign Duke of Bouillon - and his first wife [[Marie Armande Victoire de La Trémouille]]. Her mother died in 1717 and her father married three more times and had three more children.
She married [[Louis, Duke of Joyeuse (1694–1724)|Louis de Melun]], Duke of Joyeuse and Prince of Epinoy on 23 February 1716. His parents were Louis de Melun and [[Élisabeth Thérèse de Lorraine]].<ref>His sister was [[Anne Julie de Melun]], mother of the [[Charles, Prince of Soubise|Maréshal de Soubise]]'' and [[Marie Louise Geneviève de Rohan|Madame de Marsan]]</ref><ref name="La Tour">{{cite web| url= http://www.genealogics.org/getperson.php?personID=I00010752&tree=LEO | title= Armande de La Tour d'Auvergne |accessdate= 2010-04-04|last= van de Pas|first= Leo|work= Genealogics .org}}</ref>
Armande died in 1717 a month after her mother. Her husband was later the secret spouse of [[Marie Anne de Bourbon (1697–1741)|Marie Anne de Bourbon]] (1697–1741), daughter of [[Louis, Prince of Condé (1668–1710)|Monsieur le Duc]] and [[Louise-Françoise de Bourbon|Madame la Duchesse]], daughter of [[Madame de Montespan]]. Louis de Melun later disappeared in 1724 under mysterious circumstances.
==Ancestry== {{ahnentafel |collapsed=yes |align=center |boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc; |boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9; |boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc; |boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc; |boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe; |1= 1. '''Armande de La Tour d'Auvergne''' |2= 2. [[Emmanuel Theodose de La Tour d'Auvergne (1668-1730)|Emmanuel Théodose de La Tour d'Auvergne]], Duke of Bouillon |3= 3. Marie Victoire de La Trémoïlle |4= 4. [[Godefroy Maurice de La Tour d'Auvergne]], Duke of Bouillon |5= 5. [[Marie Anne Mancini]] |6= 6. [[Charles Belgique Hollande de La Trémoille]] |7= 7. Madeleine de Créquy |8= 8. [[Frédéric Maurice de La Tour d'Auvergne]], Duke of Bouillon |9= 9. Countess Eleonora van den Bergh |10= 10. [[Mancini family|Michele Lorenzo Mancini]] |11= 11. [[Girolama Mazzarini]] |12= 12. [[Henri Charles de La Trémoille|Henri Charles de La Trémoïlle]] |13= 13. Émilie of Hesse-Kassel |14= 14. Charles, Duke of Créquy |15= 15. Anne Armande de Saint-Gelais |16= 16. [[Henri de La Tour d'Auvergne, Duke of Bouillon|Henri de La Tour d'Auvergne]], Duke of Bouillon |17= 17. [[Countess Elisabeth of Nassau]] |18= 18. [[Frederik van den Bergh (1559–1618)|Frederik, Count van den Bergh]] |19= 19. Françoise de Ravenel |20= 20. Pietro Mazzarini |21= 21. Ortensia Bufalini |22= 22. Paolo Mancini |23= 23. Vittoria Capocci |24= 24. [[Henri de La Trémoille|Henri de La Trémoïlle]] |25= 25. Marie de La Tour d'Auvergne |26= 26. [[William V, Landgrave of Hesse-Kassel]] |27= 27. Amalie Elisabeth of Hanau-Münzenberg |28= 28. Charles, Duke of Créquy |29= 29. Anne Grimoard du Roure |30= 30. Gilles de Saint-Gelais, Marquess of Balon |31= 31. Marie de Vallée-Fossez, Marchioness of Everly }}
