{{other people||Ghulam Mohammad (disambiguation){{!}}Ghulam Mohammad}}

'''Ghulam Mohammed Abdul Khader''' (died 1993) was the seventh prince of the House of Arcot. He was the son of [[Ghulam Mohiuddin Khan]], the sixth [[Nawab of the Carnatic|Nawab of Arcot]] and held the title from 1969 until his death 1993. He was succeeded by the [[Muhammed Abdul Ali]] who inherited the title.

Because the Nawabs of Arcot had a special treaty with the government, this title was not abolished along with all other noble titles of India in 1972.

